<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1903-02-09T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1903-02-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="701" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d701">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Leishman</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Constantinople</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1903-02-09"><hi rend="italic">February 9,
                                1903</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>(Mr. Leishman reports that, judging from the tenor of an interview he has
                            just had at the Porte, he is inclined to believe that a few days’ more
                            patience may bring about the desired result.)</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>